Third-Party Licenses
====================

OpenMeow is licensed under the MIT License. However, the binary distribution
includes the following third-party component under a different license:


LAME MP3 Encoder
-----------------
License: LGPL-2.0 (GNU Lesser General Public License, version 2.0)
Website: https://lame.sourceforge.io/
Source:  https://sourceforge.net/projects/lame/files/lame/3.100/lame-3.100.tar.gz

OpenMeow uses LAME for MP3 audio encoding. LAME is dynamically linked as
libmp3lame.dylib and is NOT part of the OpenMeow source code. The OpenMeow
source code remains under the MIT License.

Per the terms of the LGPL-2.0, you have the right to:
  - Replace libmp3lame.dylib with a modified version
  - Obtain the LAME source code from the link above

To replace the LAME library:
  1. Right-click OpenMeow.app -> Show Package Contents
  2. Navigate to Contents/Frameworks/
  3. Replace libmp3lame.dylib with your own build
  4. Re-sign the dylib: codesign --force --sign - libmp3lame.dylib

The full text of the LGPL-2.0 license is included in the lame.xcframework
directory as LICENSE-lame, and can also be found at:
https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.0.html
